Defendant Kevin J Young in court with attorney J Anthony Rosario.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads no contest to count #3.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #3.  Counts 1 and 2 are dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Rosario makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.    The Defendant was given the following:

90 days HUBER, IMPOSED AND STAYED;  (4 days Jail Credit)
TERM OF PROBATION:  16 MONTHS;
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
No VOILENT contact with victim listed in the criminal complaint:  
COURT COSTS:  $343.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
No DNA sample/surcharge required.
